01/03/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The State Anti-corruption Commission called on the various political parties Tuesday (28 February) to observe the anti-corruption law during the upcoming election campaign.
The measure bans the use of budget funds to finance campaigns.
It also forbids new investments, new infrastructure and public projects as well as payment of unusual salaries, pensions or benefits during the election process later this year.
Also Tuesday, passenger railway traffic between Macedonia and Kosovo resumed following a six-year break.
Passenger trains will travel between Skopje and Pristina twice a day.
(A1 TV, Makfax, Telma TV - 28/02/06)
